    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fix autotune cache for CuTeDSL backend: save kernel as `kernel.py` instead of `kernel_lib.so` to prevent `importlib` from treating Python source as a native extension module\n- Add `cutedsl` branches in both `_save_kernel_to_disk` and `_load_kernel_from_disk` for correct file naming\n- Also save launcher `.so` and `.cubin` artifacts when present\n- Add `\"cutedsl\"` to `Literal` type annotations in `param.py` and `kernel.py`\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Unit test: `test_cutedsl_save_creates_kernel_py` — verifies save writes `kernel.py`, not `kernel_lib.so`\n- [x] E2E test: `test_cutedsl_autotune_cache_roundtrip` — save → clear cache → reload from disk → verify correctness\n- [x] Existing autotune tests pass (`test_tilelang_autotune.py`)\n\nCloses #1967\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Fixed CuTeDSL kernel cache persistence and reload so cached autotuned artifacts restore correctly.\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added CuTeDSL as a supported execution backend for caching and JIT loading, including handling of backend-specific cached artifacts.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added regression tests to validate CuTeDSL autotune cache persistence, disk round-trip reload, and CUDA execution correctness.\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Simplified internal dtype list representation while preserving public dtype exports.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
